For interfacing SFH3710 phototransistor to the monitor guide aperture,
optical spheres should be 6.0mm diameter, clear glass (not frosted),
transparent at visible wavelength and have a refractive index of around 1.5.

A search for "6.0mm solid glass balls" yields a plethora of available options.

https://www.alibaba.com/product-detail/High-Precision-6mm-8mm-10mm-12mm_1601265778918.html
These seem a likely candidate, however MOQ is 1kg.
(Anybody wanna buy some balls? I have a few spares.)
